{
  "texts": [
    "Data Creation for MT between dialects: Zbib et al. [2012] and Meftouh et al.",
    "[2015] also focus on multi-dialect MT data collection for Arabic, which is, once again, to be noted as one of the most studied languages for dialects.",
    "Xu et al. [2015] use a Hidden Markov-based model to create word alignment between dialects of Chinese: Mainland Chinese, Hong Kong Chinese, and Taiwan Chinese.",
    "The outcome is a monolingual corpus that contains corresponding words used in the User-generated content: User-generated content (UGC) is often mistranslated on social media, especially, for low-resource languages like dialectal Arabic.",
    "Saadany et al. [2022] train a Transformer to translate from dialectal Arabic to English where they focus on challenges in translation of UGC, and propose a sentiment-aware evaluation metric for translation."
  ]
}